OL,3,CMore checks could 'possibly' have
OL,4,Csaved teenager's life - NHS trust
OL,6,F"Despite her challenges Cariss worked
OL,7,Fso hard and she was so bright. She
OL,8,Fneeded help with learning how to cope
OL,9,Fwith her condition, and she was let
OL,10,Fdown by the services that were
OL,11,Fdesigned to support her.
OL,13,F"The fact that we as a family had to
OL,14,Fwait almost five years for an inquest
OL,15,Fis completely unacceptable and the
OL,16,Fpassage of time hindered the quality
OL,17,Fof the investigation in numerous ways.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/10
